    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sobol sensitivity analysis — hemolysis power-law and viscosity parameters",
    "description": "A variance-based Sobol sensitivity analysis was conducted on the hemolysis prediction model, varying the power-law stress exponent (α ∈ [0.62, 0.82]), the strain-rate coefficient (C ∈ [1.8×10⁻⁶, 2.4×10⁻⁶]), and blood dynamic viscosity (μ ∈ [0.0033, 0.0042] Pa·s) across 2048 quasi-random samples. First-order Sobol indices indicate that α accounts for 61% of output variance in NIH, μ accounts for 22%, and C accounts for 14%; interaction terms contribute the remaining 3%. This confirms that uncertainty in the stress exponent is the dominant driver of hemolysis prediction uncertainty and motivates targeted experimental characterization of α."
  },
