      "rationale": "The hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) and SST k-ω turbulence closure were selected based on systematic literature review of blood pump CFD studies. Alternative turbulence models (k-ε realizable, LES) were evaluated on a subset of operating points; SST k-ω showed lowest NIH prediction error. Model form uncertainty was quantified by comparing NIH predictions across three hemolysis model variants; spread of 12% was incorporated into the total uncertainty budget.",
