      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis measurements were conducted on n=6 independent test runs per operating point using fresh porcine blood from three separate donors, providing biological replicate coverage. Statistical analysis confirmed no significant donor-to-donor variability (ANOVA p=0.31). Sample size was determined by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect a 10% NIH difference.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/test-samples-mrl5",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "Minimum n=3 biological replicates per operating point; power analysis documented; inter-donor variability assessed by ANOVA; coefficient of variation in NIH across replicates < 20%."
      }
